  "summary": "Malicious code in nullrift (npm)",
  "details": "Nullrift@1.0.0 is a trojanized SVG sanitizer utility. The index.js exports a getPlugin() function that, when invoked, sends an HTTPS GET to hxxps://www[.]jsonkeeper[.]com/b/3P9BF with a custom header (bearrtoken: \"logo\"), parses the JSON response, and executes the value of the 'model' field via eval(). This enables arbitrary remote code execution from a third-party JSON-hosting service, which can serve updated payloads at any time. The package also contains a decoy SVG sanitization module to appear legitimate.",
